				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
			
			<div id='uael-faq-wrapper-238' class="uael-faq-wrapper">
				<div class="uael-faq-container uael-faq-layout-accordion" data-layout="accordion" >
												<div id="uael-accordion-316beab" class="uael-faq-accordion" role="tablist">
								<div class= "uael-accordion-title" aria-expanded="false" role="tab">
									<span class="uael-accordion-icon uael-accordion-icon-left">
										<span class="uael-accordion-icon-closed"><i class="fas fa-angle-right"></i></span>
										<span class="uael-accordion-icon-opened"><i class="fas fa-angle-up"></i></span>
									</span>
									<span class="uael-question-316beab uael-question-span" tabindex="0" id="uael-faq-1">Are restaurants profitable?</span>
								</div>
								<div class="uael-accordion-content" role="tabpanel">
									<span>
									<span><p>Restaurants' profitability levels range between 0% and 10% (measured by net income, after paying taxes). However, many restaurants can be reliable sources of cash flow.</p></span>									</span>
								</div>
							</div>
														<div id="uael-accordion-e2ed746" class="uael-faq-accordion" role="tablist">
								<div class= "uael-accordion-title" aria-expanded="false" role="tab">
									<span class="uael-accordion-icon uael-accordion-icon-left">
										<span class="uael-accordion-icon-closed"><i class="fas fa-angle-right"></i></span>
										<span class="uael-accordion-icon-opened"><i class="fas fa-angle-up"></i></span>
									</span>
									<span class="uael-question-e2ed746 uael-question-span" tabindex="0" id="uael-faq-2">What are the most profitable restaurants?</span>
								</div>
								<div class="uael-accordion-content" role="tabpanel">
									<span>
									<span><p>Highly franchised quick-service restaurants (usually known as fast-food) tend to have the highest profitability (close to 25% of EBITDA margin).</p></span>									</span>
								</div>
							</div>
														<div id="uael-accordion-9726b88" class="uael-faq-accordion" role="tablist">
								<div class= "uael-accordion-title" aria-expanded="false" role="tab">
									<span class="uael-accordion-icon uael-accordion-icon-left">
										<span class="uael-accordion-icon-closed"><i class="fas fa-angle-right"></i></span>
										<span class="uael-accordion-icon-opened"><i class="fas fa-angle-up"></i></span>
									</span>
									<span class="uael-question-9726b88 uael-question-span" tabindex="0" id="uael-faq-3">Why are restaurant profit margins so low?</span>
								</div>
								<div class="uael-accordion-content" role="tabpanel">
									<span>
									<span><p>The cost of food and labor are usually stable at close to 30% of revenue each. That takes a significant portion of a restaurant profits. Other expenses such as rent, utilities, SG&amp;A (the overhead needed to administer the restaurant, especially for chains), and taxes detract from restaurant profits.  </p></span>									</span>
								</div>
							</div>
														<div id="uael-accordion-89063df" class="uael-faq-accordion" role="tablist">
								<div class= "uael-accordion-title" aria-expanded="false" role="tab">
									<span class="uael-accordion-icon uael-accordion-icon-left">
